Module org.microbean.type
Package org.microbean.type

Class JavaTypeSet

java.lang.Object
java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
java.util.AbstractSet<Type>
org.microbean.type.JavaTypeSet
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<Type>, Collection<Type>, Set<Type>
public final class JavaTypeSet extends AbstractSet<Type>
An immutable AbstractSet of Types that ensures that Type implementations from different vendors use the same equality semantics.
Author:
Laird Nelson

    • mostSpecializedNonInterfaceType

      public final Type mostSpecializedNonInterfaceType()
      Returns an arbitrarily selected Type that is guaranteed to represent the most specialized subclass drawn from the types in this JavaTypeSet.

      For example, if a JavaTypeSet contains Integer.class, Number.class and Object.class, then this method will return Integer.class. If a JavaTypeSet contains Integer.class and String.class, then either Integer.class or String.class will be returned.

      In practice, most JavaTypeSets in normal use contain classes from a single inheritance hierarchy.

      Returns:
      an arbitrarily selected Type that is guaranteed to represent the most specialized subclass in its type hierarchy drawn from the types in this JavaTypeSet; never null; the Type returned is guaranteed to be either a Class or a ParameterizedType
      See Also:
      • mostSpecializedInterfaceType()
      Idempotency:
      This method is idempotent but deterministic only in certain cases.
      Nullability:
      This method never returns null.
      Thread Safety:
      This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple threads.

    • mostSpecializedInterfaceType

      public final Type mostSpecializedInterfaceType()
      Returns an arbitrarily selected Type that is guaranteed to be a Type representing the most specialized interface drawn from types representing interfaces in this JavaTypeSet, or null if this JavaTypeSet contains no interfaces.

      The Class that is represented indirectly by the return value, if any, is guaranteed to return true from its Class.isInterface() method.

      For example, if a JavaTypeSet contains Closeable.class and AutoCloseable.class, then this method will return Closeable.class. If a JavaTypeSet contains AutoCloseable.class and Serializable.class, then either AutoCloseable.class or Serializable.class will be returned.

      Returns:
      an arbitrarily selected Type that is guaranteed to be a Type representing the most specialized interface drawn from types representing interfaces in this JavaTypeSet, or null; the Type returned is guaranteed to be either a Class or a ParameterizedType
      See Also:
      • mostSpecializedNonInterfaceType()
      Idempotency:
      This method is idempotent but deterministic only in certain cases.
      Nullability:
      This method may return null.
      Thread Safety:
      This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple threads.
